virtualenv env --system-site-packages

source env/bin/activate

pip3 install --upgrade jupyter matplotlib numpy pandas scipy scikit-learn

Fire Jupyter
jupyter notebook


The hist() method relies on Matplotlib, which in turn relies on a user-specified graphical backend to draw on screen
%matplotlib line
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
data.hist(bins=50, figsize=(20,15)
plt.show()

Above uses Jupyter's magic command %matplotlib line which tells Jupyter to set up Matplotlib so it uses Jupyter's own backend
